# Optional: full path to LibreOffice soffice (for PDF export from DOCX)
# Windows example: LIBREOFFICE_PATH="C:\\Program Files\\LibreOffice\\program\\soffice.exe"
# LIBREOFFICE_PATH=

# Faster PDF conversion: run a LibreOffice listener and use unoconv (avoids starting LibreOffice each time)
# 1. Start listener in a separate terminal: soffice --headless --accept="socket,host=127.0.0.1,port=2083;urp;StarOffice.ServiceManager"
# 2. Install unoconv (e.g. pip install unoconv, or your OS package manager)
# 3. Set the following and ensure unoconv is in PATH or set UNOCONV_PATH:
# LIBREOFFICE_USE_LISTENER=true
# LIBREOFFICE_LISTENER_HOST=127.0.0.1
# LIBREOFFICE_LISTENER_PORT=2083
# UNOCONV_PATH=
